Sales Manager Job (Manufacturing Industrial Equipment), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of a leading multinational company with a core focus on Industrial equipment such as Heat Transfer, Separation and Fluid Handling. Our established client has been present in Indonesia since 1993. As expansion continues, our client is seeking a sales professional for the job of Sales Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.  Key job responsibilities will include: Develops a business plan and sales strategy, including marcom activities, for the market that ensures attainment of company sales goals and profitabilityOrders received, gross margin and net invoicingPerformance and development of the sales engineer/MU ManagerInitiates and coordinates development of action plans to penetrate new marketsAssists in the development and implementation of marketing plans as needed                                                         Determination of a pricing strategy                                       Setting and implementation of the pricing policy and authorizationProvides timely, accurate, competitive pricing on all completed prospect applications submitted for pricing and approval, while striving to maintain maximum profit marginResolving product or service problems and disruptions and customer complaints during warranty period of unit or partsVisit customer to maintain good relationship as neededCreates and conducts proposal presentationsControls expenses to meet budget guidelinesProvides all necessary reports including forecasts in an accurate and timely manner                       Adheres to all company policies, procedures and business ethics codes and ensures that they are communicated and implemented within the team Job Requirements Bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering or related major from a reputable universityAt least 10 years’ experience preferably related to oil and gas industryProficient in Microsoft Office (MS Project, MS Word, MS Excel…)Good verbal and written command of EnglishAbility to perform effectively under pressure and manage competing priorities to achieve project deadlinesSelf-motivated and capable of working with minimum direct supervisionAbility to adapt to changing circumstancesLeadership skills are required to marshal resources and lead the teamsMust oversee appropriate communication as necessary All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to industrial@monroeconsulting.com
